HEADWORD: Crenation
<hw>Cre*na"tion</hw> <pr>(kr?-n?"sh?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A rounded tooth on the edge of a leaf.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The condition of being crenate.</def>⟦br⟧
